diks info--------------------------------------------
fdisk -l
fdisk -l | grep 'Disk /dev'
or df -h
or lsblk

sudo fdisk /dev/sda //for partition

cpu info---------------------------------------------
nproc = cpu count
lscpu = cpu cpunt with details
top = displays the processes used by different users 
sudo cat /proc/cpuinfo = cpu deatails in file



ram info-----------------------------------------
free = display as byte
free -m = display as mb
vmstat -s = display as details